[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6921,
        "end_time": 10123,
        "text": "Imagine setting sail \nfrom Hawaii in a canoe."
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 10123,
        "end_time": 13960,
        "text": "Your target is a small island thousands\nof kilometers away"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 13960,
        "end_time": 16512,
        "text": "in the middle of the Pacific Ocean."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 16512,
        "end_time": 21252,
        "text": "That&#39;s a body of water that covers\nmore than 160 million square kilometers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 21252,
        "end_time": 26352,
        "text": "greater than all the landmasses \non Earth combined."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 26352,
        "end_time": 27541,
        "text": "For thousands of years,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 27541,
        "end_time": 30932,
        "text": "Polynesian navigators managed voyages \nlike this"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 30932,
        "end_time": 34342,
        "text": "without the help \nof modern navigational aids."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 34342,
        "end_time": 36241,
        "text": "Ancient Polynesians used the Sun,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 36241,
        "end_time": 37052,
        "text": "Moon,"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 37052,
        "end_time": 37871,
        "text": "stars,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 37871,
        "end_time": 38651,
        "text": "planets,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 38651,
        "end_time": 39633,
        "text": "ocean currents,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 39633,
        "end_time": 45993,
        "text": "and clouds as guides that allowed them\nto see the ocean as a series of pathways"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 45993,
        "end_time": 48982,
        "text": "rather than an obstacle."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 48982,
        "end_time": 52073,
        "text": "Their voyages began around 1500 B.C."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 52073,
        "end_time": 57574,
        "text": "when the people who would settle Polynesia\nfirst set sail from Southeast Asia."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 57574,
        "end_time": 61487,
        "text": "Early Polynesians eventually settled\na vast area of islands"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 61487,
        "end_time": 66743,
        "text": "spread over 40 million square kilometers\nof the Pacific Ocean."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 66743,
        "end_time": 70109,
        "text": "Some historians believe the voyagers moved\nfrom place to place"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 70109,
        "end_time": 71874,
        "text": "to avoid overpopulation."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 71874,
        "end_time": 74015,
        "text": "Others, that they were driven by war."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 74015,
        "end_time": 78286,
        "text": "Voyages became less frequent\nby around 1300 A.D."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 78286,
        "end_time": 84335,
        "text": "as Polynesian societies became more rooted\nin specific locations."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 84335,
        "end_time": 85975,
        "text": "During the voyaging period,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 85975,
        "end_time": 89265,
        "text": "successful journeys depended on \na number of factors:"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 89265,
        "end_time": 90655,
        "text": "well-built canoes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 90655,
        "end_time": 92294,
        "text": "the skill of navigators,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 92294,
        "end_time": 95425,
        "text": "and weather being some of the biggest."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 95425,
        "end_time": 99876,
        "text": "Voyages relied on sturdy wa&#39;a kaulua,\nor double-hulled canoes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 99876,
        "end_time": 104635,
        "text": "which were powered by sails\nand steered with a single large oar."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 104635,
        "end_time": 107016,
        "text": "Canoe building involved\nthe whole community,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 107016,
        "end_time": 108665,
        "text": "bringing together the navigators,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 108665,
        "end_time": 109745,
        "text": "canoe builders,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 109745,
        "end_time": 110656,
        "text": "priests,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 110656,
        "end_time": 111522,
        "text": "chanters,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 111522,
        "end_time": 113846,
        "text": "and hula dancers."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 113846,
        "end_time": 117096,
        "text": "Navigators were keen observers \nof the natural world."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 117096,
        "end_time": 121536,
        "text": "They were abundantly familiar with \ntrade wind-generated ocean swells,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 121536,
        "end_time": 125058,
        "text": "which typically flow \nnortheast or southeast."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 125058,
        "end_time": 127528,
        "text": "By day, navigators could \nidentify direction"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 127528,
        "end_time": 131606,
        "text": "by the rocking motion of their canoes\ncaused by these swells."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 131606,
        "end_time": 135217,
        "text": "But sunrise and sunset \nwere even more useful."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 135217,
        "end_time": 138588,
        "text": "The Sun&#39;s position indicated east and west"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 138588,
        "end_time": 144888,
        "text": "and created low light on the ocean that\nmade it possible to see swells directly."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 144888,
        "end_time": 148618,
        "text": "At night, navigators used something \ncalled a star compass,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 148618,
        "end_time": 153497,
        "text": "which wasn&#39;t a physical object,\nbut rather a sort of mental map."
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 153497,
        "end_time": 157917,
        "text": "They memorized the rising and setting\npoints of stars and constellations"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 157917,
        "end_time": 160317,
        "text": "at different times of the year."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 160317,
        "end_time": 163528,
        "text": "They used those to divide the sky\ninto four quadrants,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 163528,
        "end_time": 166879,
        "text": "subdivided into 32 houses,"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 166879,
        "end_time": 168908,
        "text": "with the canoe in the middle."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 168908,
        "end_time": 173479,
        "text": "So, for example, when they saw the star\nPira\u2018atea rising from the ocean,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 173479,
        "end_time": 175480,
        "text": "they knew that to be northeast."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 175484,
        "end_time": 177997,
        "text": "They had some other tricks, too."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 177997,
        "end_time": 182657,
        "text": "The Earth&#39;s axis points towards Hokupa&#39;a,\nor the North Star,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 182657,
        "end_time": 187085,
        "text": "so called because it&#39;s the one fixed\npoint in the sky as the Earth rotates"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 187085,
        "end_time": 189395,
        "text": "and always indicates north."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 189395,
        "end_time": 192165,
        "text": "However, it&#39;s not visible \nsouth of the Equator,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 192165,
        "end_time": 195715,
        "text": "so navigators there could use\na constellation called Newe,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 195715,
        "end_time": 197424,
        "text": "or the Southern Cross,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 197424,
        "end_time": 201096,
        "text": "and some mental tricks to estimate\nwhere south is."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 201096,
        "end_time": 204635,
        "text": "For instance, draw a line through\nthese two stars,"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 204635,
        "end_time": 206695,
        "text": "extend it 4.5 times,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 206695,
        "end_time": 209574,
        "text": "and draw another line \nfrom there to the horizon."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 209574,
        "end_time": 211097,
        "text": "That&#39;s south."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 211097,
        "end_time": 216806,
        "text": "But the sky also contains \nnavigational aids much closer to Earth,"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 216806,
        "end_time": 218478,
        "text": "the clouds."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 218478,
        "end_time": 220397,
        "text": "Besides being useful weather cues,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 220397,
        "end_time": 223917,
        "text": "under the right conditions, \nthey can indicate landmasses."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 223917,
        "end_time": 227116,
        "text": "For instance, the lagoons \nof Pacific atolls"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 227116,
        "end_time": 231488,
        "text": "can actually be seen reflected\non the underside of clouds,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 231488,
        "end_time": 233498,
        "text": "if you know what to look for."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 233498,
        "end_time": 238627,
        "text": "And high masses of clouds can indicate\nmountainous islands."
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 238627,
        "end_time": 241377,
        "text": "Once navigators neared their destination,\nother clues,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 241377,
        "end_time": 244088,
        "text": "such as the flight patterns of birds,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 244088,
        "end_time": 246007,
        "text": "floating debris or vegetation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 246007,
        "end_time": 251468,
        "text": "and types of fish in the area helped\ndetermine the proximity of land."
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 251468,
        "end_time": 256938,
        "text": "For example, the Manu-O-Ku had a known\nflight range of 190 kilometers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 256938,
        "end_time": 259838,
        "text": "and could be followed back to shore."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 259838,
        "end_time": 262287,
        "text": "So how do we know all of this?"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 262287,
        "end_time": 264570,
        "text": "Partially through evidence in petroglyphs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 264570,
        "end_time": 267198,
        "text": "written observations \nof European explorers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 267198,
        "end_time": 270099,
        "text": "and Polynesian oral traditions."
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 270099,
        "end_time": 273588,
        "text": "But also by trying them out for ourselves."
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 273588,
        "end_time": 277079,
        "text": "In 2017, a voyaging canoe called Hokulea"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 277079,
        "end_time": 282319,
        "text": "completed a worldwide voyage \nusing only these techniques."
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 282319,
        "end_time": 286079,
        "text": "If that seems remarkable,\nremember the ancient Polynesians,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 286079,
        "end_time": 288979,
        "text": "who through close study \nand kinship with nature,"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 288979,
        "end_time": 291360,
        "text": "were able to forge these paths across"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 291360,
        "end_time": 295250,
        "text": "an unfathomably vast, \nvibrant living ocean."
    }
]